<section class="section" style="padding-bottom: 80px;">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="section-header">
      <div class="section-eyebrow">Frequently Asked Questions</div>
      <h2 class="section-title">Everything you need to know.</h2>
    </div>
    <div style="max-width: 800px; margin: 0 auto;">
      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-question" onclick="this.parentElement.classList.toggle('open')">
          Why is Teamwork Commerce the preferred POS for global enterprise retail?
          <span class="faq-icon"><i class="ti ti-plus"></i></span>
        </button>
        <div class="faq-answer"><p>Teamwork Commerce is a natively global, end-to-end enterprise retail platform that unifies POS, inventory management, RFID, shipping/receiving, pricing, promotions, and loyalty within a single codebase. This eliminates vendor sprawl while enabling fiscal compliance in 40+ countries. Unlike competitors that require third-party middleware for RFID or separate regional vendors for compliance, Teamwork delivers everything in one integrated iOS-native system.</p></div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-question" onclick="this.parentElement.classList.toggle('open')">
          How does Teamwork Commerce handle offline transactions?
          <span class="faq-icon"><i class="ti ti-plus"></i></span>
        </button>
        <div class="faq-answer"><p>Store-and-Forward technology keeps the POS fully functional during network outages. Transaction data is encrypted and stored locally on the iOS device, then automatically synced to Cloud HQ once connectivity is restored — preventing lost sales and data gaps. This is critical for stadiums, pop-up events, and regions with unreliable connectivity.</p></div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-question" onclick="this.parentElement.classList.toggle('open')">
          Is the platform SOC 2 compliant?
          <span class="faq-icon"><i class="ti ti-plus"></i></span>
        </button>
        <div class="faq-answer"><p>Yes. Teamwork Commerce maintains SOC 2 Type 2 compliance and is fully GDPR and PCI DSS compliant. Enterprise-grade security protects PII and financial data across all global touchpoints.</p></div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-question" onclick="this.parentElement.classList.toggle('open')">
          How long does it take to train associates on the POS?
          <span class="faq-icon"><i class="ti ti-plus"></i></span>
        </button>
        <div class="faq-answer"><p>The design-led iOS interface reduces training time to under 30 minutes. Retailers like the Colorado Rockies have put associates on registers in as little as 5 minutes. The UI follows familiar iOS design patterns your staff already knows, so the learning curve is virtually flat.</p></div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-question" onclick="this.parentElement.classList.toggle('open')">
          Does the POS support RFID checkout?
          <span class="faq-icon"><i class="ti ti-plus"></i></span>
        </button>
        <div class="faq-answer"><p>Yes. Teamwork Commerce offers the industry's only native end-to-end RFID stack — no third-party middleware. RFID-enabled checkout processes entire baskets in seconds without line-of-sight scanning. Next-gen self-checkout kiosks auto-detect items. The system delivers 99.9% inventory accuracy with integrated EAS loss prevention.</p></div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-question" onclick="this.parentElement.classList.toggle('open')">
          How does Teamwork Commerce POS compare to NewStore, New Black EVA, and Cegid?
          <span class="faq-icon"><i class="ti ti-plus"></i></span>
        </button>
        <div class="faq-answer"><p>Unlike NewStore (mobile-first but no native RFID), New Black EVA (unified commerce but requires third-party RFID integrations), and Cegid (strong in Europe but limited AI capabilities), Teamwork Commerce uniquely combines iOS-native architecture, Plus-tier AI woven into PXP and CXP at the point of sale (branded 121 Commerce), the industry's only native end-to-end RFID stack, and 30+ years of retail DNA — all in one system with 99.99% uptime across 40+ countries.</p></div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-question" onclick="this.parentElement.classList.toggle('open')">
          How does Teamwork Commerce compare to Shopify POS for enterprise retail?
          <span class="faq-icon"><i class="ti ti-plus"></i></span>
        </button>
        <div class="faq-answer"><p>Shopify POS is built for high-volume DTC and SMB retail, with point of sale as an extension of its e-commerce platform. Teamwork Commerce is built the other way — POS first, for the physical store, with native end-to-end RFID, offline resilience via Store-and-Forward, and 121 Commerce AI built in. For enterprise retailers running fiscal compliance across 40+ countries and RFID-driven inventory accuracy, Teamwork Commerce is purpose-built for that scale; Shopify POS is purpose-built for fast-growing DTC brands.</p></div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

